The paper proposes a new method for compressing a special type of text where the order of the rows makes no difference. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the data structures (cs.DS) or information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of traditional lossless compression methods, which could also place it in the sub-categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) or cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper compares its results to existing compression methods, which could indicate that it belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
